&lt;h3 class="relative group">A bit of information 
 &lt;div id="a-bit-of-information" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
 &lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
 style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#a-bit-of-information" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
 &lt;/span> 
 
&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://aur.chaotic.cx" target="_blank">&lt;strong>Chaotic-AUR&lt;/strong>&lt;/a> is an unofficial package repository that contains pre-built packages from the &lt;strong>Arch User Repository&lt;/strong> (AUR) . It is an automated building service that compiles AUR packages so users don&amp;rsquo;t have to build them themselves.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Chaotic-AUR&lt;/strong> is a convenient way to access AUR packages without having to build them yourself, but users should still exercise caution and verify the packages, as it is an unofficial repository&lt;/p>


 
